# 04 - Commands Used (Day 1)

## 📌 Linux Log Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `cd /var/log` | Go to the log directory |
| `ls -lh` | List log files |
| `cat /var/log/auth.log` | View the entire authentication log |
| `head -20 /var/log/auth.log` | View the first 20 lines |
| `tail -20 /var/log/auth.log` | View the last 20 lines |
| `tail -f /var/log/auth.log` | Monitor logs in real time |
| `grep ssh /var/log/auth.log` | Search for SSH login events |
| `grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log` | Find failed login attempts |
| `last` | View successful login history (`wtmp`) |
| `sudo lastb` | View failed login history (`btmp`) |
| `lastlog` | Display the last login of all users |

## ✅ Key Takeaway

These are the basic commands every SOC Analyst uses to:
- Investigate authentication logs
- Detect failed login attempts
- Monitor user activity
- Analyze security incidents
